The paper proposes a new paradigm for traffic assignment in a Mobility as a Service (MaaS) network of multiple operators using the concept of stable matching to allocate costs and determine prices offered by operators corresponding to user route choices and operator service choices. This involves game theory and optimization techniques, which are commonly found in the computer science sub-categories of cs.GT (Game Theory), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with network optimization and traffic assignment, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
